One possible schema for this database is as follows:

Collection: expenses
Document schema:
- id (auto-generated)
- name: String
- description: String (optional)
- months: Map<String, Map<String, Map<String, Map<String, Double>>>>
  - keys: 12 months (e.g. "January", "February", etc.)
  - values: maps with keys being numbers representing each day of the month (e.g. "1", "2", "3", etc.), and values being maps with keys "name", "quantity", and "price", and values being the corresponding data types (String, Int, Double).

Example document:
{
  name: "Groceries",
  description: "Expenses related to food and household supplies",
  months: {
    "January": {
      "1": {
        "item1": {
          name: "Apples",
          quantity: 2,
          price: 1.99
        },
        "item2": {
          name: "Bread",
          quantity: 1,
          price: 2.49
        }
      },
      "2": {
        "item1": {
          name: "Milk",
          quantity: 1,
          price: 3.25
        }
      },
      //... rest of the days of January
    },
    "February": {
      // ... items for February
    },
    // ... rest of the months
  }
} 

This schema allows for efficient querying of expenses by month or day, while also allowing for flexibility in adding or removing items for each day without having to rewrite the entire document.

